==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: nationalist
<hw>na"tion*al*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
advocates national unity and independence; -- as, for example, one of a
party favoring Irish independence before 1918.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who advocates nationalism, in any
sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>nationalistic</ent>⟦br⟧
